# Project Summary

## Overview

During my IT Security Infrastructure internship, I worked on improving the operational reliability and efficiency of enterprise SOC platforms. My responsibilities included supporting security tooling, improving documentation governance, optimizing data ingestion processes, and resolving integration issues across multiple security systems.

## Problems Addressed

Security operations environments often face challenges related to data volume, system integration, and access governance. Some key challenges included:

High ingestion volume creating operational overhead  
Complex documentation access roles  
Integration issues between security tools  
Endpoint interoperability issues  

These issues can impact SOC efficiency and security visibility.

## Actions Taken

My work included:

- Maintaining operational health of SOC platforms including Splunk, NetWitness, and SentinelOne

- Troubleshooting ingestion, indexing, and API integration issues

- Supporting migration of SOC documentation to infrastructure ownership

- Consolidating documentation access roles from 22 roles to 11 roles to improve governance

- Supporting least privilege enforcement improvements

- Configuring Gigamon fabric maps enabling HTTPS packet slicing and deduplication

- Supporting SentinelOne endpoint policy troubleshooting through targeted exclusions

## Results

My work contributed to measurable improvements including:

- 53.6% reduction in NetWitness ingestion volume

- Improved cost efficiency through data optimization

- Improved governance through role consolidation

- Improved security documentation organization

- Prevention of workflow disruptions across mission critical systems

- Improved SOC platform stability

